.TH POROS 1 "December 2025" "poros 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
poros \- modern, cross-platform network path tracer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B poros
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fITARGET\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Poros
(Greek: Πόρος - "path, passage") is a modern network path tracer that traces
the route packets take to reach a destination host. It shows each hop along
the path with timing information, ASN data, and geographic location.
.PP
Features include multiple probe methods (ICMP, UDP, TCP SYN, Paris),
concurrent probing, ASN/GeoIP enrichment, and interactive TUI mode.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Probe Methods"
.TP
.BR \-I ", " \-\-icmp
Use ICMP Echo probes (default)
.TP
.BR \-U ", " \-\-udp
Use UDP probes
.TP
.BR \-T ", " \-\-tcp
Use TCP SYN probes
.TP
.B \-\-paris
Use Paris traceroute algorithm (load-balancer friendly)
.SS "Trace Parameters"
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-max\-hops " " \fIN\fR
Maximum number of hops (default: 30)
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-queries " " \fIN\fR
Number of probes per hop (default: 3)
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-timeout " " \fIDURATION\fR
Probe timeout (default: 3s)
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-first\-hop " " \fIN\fR
Start from specified hop (default: 1)
.TP
.B \-\-sequential
Use sequential mode instead of concurrent
.SS "Network Settings"
.TP
.BR \-4 ", " \-\-ipv4
Use IPv4 only
.TP
.BR \-6 ", " \-\-ipv6
Use IPv6 only
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Destination port for UDP/TCP (default: 33434)
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interface " " \fINAME\fR
Network interface to use
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-source " " \fIIP\fR
Source IP address
.SS "Output Formats"
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show detailed table output
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-json
Output in JSON format
.TP
.B \-\-csv
Output in CSV format
.TP
.BI \-\-html " FILE"
Generate HTML report to file
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-tui
Interactive TUI mode
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable colored output
.SS "Enrichment"
.TP
.B \-\-no\-enrich
Disable all enrichment
.TP
.B \-\-no\-rdns
Disable reverse DNS lookups
.TP
.B \-\-no\-asn
Disable ASN lookups
.TP
.B \-\-no\-geoip
Disable GeoIP lookups
.SS "Other"
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message
.TP
.B version
Show version information
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic ICMP trace:
.B poros google.com
.TP
UDP probe mode:
.B poros \-U google.com
.TP
TCP SYN to port 443:
.B poros \-T \-p 443 google.com
.TP
Paris traceroute:
.B poros \-\-paris google.com
.TP
Verbose table output:
.B poros \-v google.com
.TP
JSON output:
.B poros \-\-json google.com
.TP
Interactive TUI:
.B poros \-\-tui google.com
.TP
HTML report:
.B poros \-\-html report.html google.com
.SH PRIVILEGES
Raw sockets require elevated privileges:
.TP
.B Linux
Run with sudo or set CAP_NET_RAW capability:
.br
.B sudo setcap cap_net_raw+ep /path/to/poros
.TP
.B macOS
Run with sudo
.TP
.B Windows
Run as Administrator
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (network unreachable, permission denied, etc.)
